The paper discusses the use of machine learning models in a medical setting, specifically in the ICU. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of Bayesian modelling and predictive uncertainty, which are relevant to the sub-categories of computational engineering (cs.CE) and cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper applies a Bayesian Neural Network to a medical dataset, which is relevant to the sub-category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
